        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 5:17PM EDT by NWS Tallahassee FL</headline>
        <description>At 517 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Willacoochee, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Glory and Bannockburn.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
